{"id":"life","term":"Life","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Generally of physical life (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:7\">Gen. 2:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Luke 16:25\">Luke 16:25</a>, etc.); also used figuratively (1) for immortality (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hebrews 7:16\">Heb. 7:16</a>); (2) conduct or manner of life (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 6:4\">Rom. 6:4</a>); (3) spiritual life or salvation (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 3:16\">John 3:16</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 3:17\">17</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 3:18\">18</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 3:36\">36</a>); (4) eternal life (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 19:16\">Matt. 19:16</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 19:17\">17</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 3:15\">John 3:15</a>); of God and Christ as the absolute source and cause of all life (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 1:4\">John 1:4</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 5:26\">5:26</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 5:39\">39</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 11:25\">11:25</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"John 12:50\">12:50</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 2:7","Luke 16:25","Hebrews 7:16","Romans 6:4","John 3:16","John 3:17","John 3:18","John 3:36","Matthew 19:16","Matthew 19:17","John 3:15","John 1:4","John 5:26","John 5:39","John 11:25","John 12:50"]}